(71, 1, '2014-03-06 13:22:37', '2014-03-06 13:22:37', 'In registering to the iCommunity platform using this website, you agree to be bound by the Terms and Conditions (the "Terms") set out below. If you do not agree to the Terms then you may not register to the Central Community  platform nor use this platform.\r\n \r\n1. Definitions:\r\n"Platform" means the Central Community  platform at the following URL: http://gaia.cybion.eu/cecommunity \r\n"You/Your" means the registrant to the platform and/or user of this platform.\r\n"User Information" refers to information provided by you via the platform.\r\n"We/Us/Our" means the manager of the Central Community  platform\r\n\r\n2. Registration\r\n2.1\r\nYou agree that the User Information which You provide when You register is true, accurate, current and complete in all respects and You agree to notify Us as soon as possible of any changes to the User Information by amending Your User Information online within the Profile Administration section of the Website.\r\nYou understand and agree to the following: (a) if you register, you must submit a valid e-mail address and select a password during the registration process; (b) You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your password; (c) You agree to notify Central Community  users immediately of any unauthorized use of your account, (d) You are of legal age, (e) You agree to provide certain limited information about you as prompted to do so by Central Community (such information to be current, complete and accurate); and (f) maintain and update this information as required to keep it current, complete and accurate.\r\nWe reserve the right to delete accounts created by users who appropriate the name, likeness, email address, or other personally identifiable information of another individual. All illegal and deceptive user ID is deleted as soon as we obtain actual knowledge about it. If your name, or other personally identifiable information are misleading we have the right to verify the users identity, by asking other information about the user to avoid misleading ID use. You understand and agree to answer the verifying e-mail in 24 hours, otherwise your account will be deleted. As soon as we obtain actual knowledge about assumed misleading user ID, we have the right to restrict the account of users until the end of the verifying process.\r\n\r\nWe will not be held liable for any loss or damage for non-compliance. In addition, you understand and agree that the content of all users, including your content, will be collected, aggregated and anonymously integrated into Central Community and that Central Community will use aggregated data collected from you and other users for anonymous statistical and analytical reporting purposes. You understand, and agree that, unless expressly stated, Central Community in no way controls, verifies, or endorses any of the information on Central Community Platform.\r\nCentral Community reserves the right to refuse the Service to any user.\r\nThe official languages of Central Community is are and all official notices should be sent in this language.\r\n\r\n2.2\r\nYou will be required to select a password during the registration process. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of the password and are fully responsible for all activities that occur under them during Your use of the Website. You agree not to share Your password with others or allow access to multiple users through a single password.\r\n\r\n2.3\r\nWe reserve the right to decline any registration from You to the platform at Our sole discretion.\r\n\r\n3. Copyright and database rights\r\n3.1\r\nAll rights, title, and interest (including all copyrights and other intellectual property rights) in the platform belong to Us. You acquire no proprietary interest in the platform by using it, registering therein or attending an event run by us.\r\n\r\n3.2\r\nYou are fully responsible for any content you post on the platform, including, but not limited to, photos, personal profile(s), discussion posts, listings, ratings, personal messages - and the consequences of any such content.\r\nThe platform does not control the content provided by the users. Central Community as an intermediary service provider is not liable for the information transmitted.\r\nYou understand and agree that we may remove Materials without any notice that we determine, in our sole discretion, are unlawful, fraudulent, threatening, libelous, defamatory, obscene or otherwise objectionable, or infringes or violates any party''s intellectual property or other proprietary rights or these Terms of Service in case of we obtain actual knowledge about illegal activity. In this case we may delete user account without any notices.\r\n		\r\nExamples of illegal or unauthorized uses include, but are not limited to:\r\n		\r\n●	modifying, adapting, or reverse engineering any portion of the Central Community service;\r\n●	using any robot, spider, site search/retrieval application, or other device to retrieve or index any portion or the Central Community service;\r\n●	collecting any information about other Members (including usernames and/or email addresses) for unauthorized purposes;\r\n●	reformatting or framing any portion of the web pages that are part of the Central Community service;\r\n●	creating user accounts by automated means or under false or fraudulent pretenses;\r\n●	creating or transmitting unwanted electronic communications such as "spam," or chain letters to other Members or otherwise interfering with other Member''s enjoyment of the service;\r\n●	submitting Materials that falsely express or imply that such Materials are sponsored or endorsed by Central Community;\r\n●	submitting Materials that infringe, misappropriate or violate the intellectual property, publicity, privacy or other proprietary rights of any party;\r\n●	transmitting any viruses, worms, defects, Trojan horses or other items of a destructive nature;\r\n●	submitting Materials that are unlawful or promote or encourage illegal activity;\r\n●	submitting false or misleading information.\r\n\r\nIn particular but without limitation no person shall download or otherwise extract substantive amounts of information concerning registered users or their companies and make such data available to third parties who would not otherwise have access to such collated information.\r\n\r\n4. Your Obligations\r\n4.1\r\nYou agree that You will only use the platform in a manner that is consistent with these Terms and any Additional Terms and in such a way as to ensure compliance with all applicable laws and regulations (including without limitation Your local law as far as it is applicable).\r\n\r\n4.2\r\nTo the extent to which Your use or the use by any person who may be authorised by You or for whom You are responsible (for example, as employer) causes loss or damage to Us or any person, You agree to indemnify Us immediately on demand in relation to any such losses or damages attributable to them, including where necessary any legal, administrative or technical charges that may arise from such use.\r\n\r\n4.3\r\nYou are responsible for the content you create for your profile. The information must be true, and must not violate any rights or offend against dignity. Otherwise we are authorized to delete your profile.\r\n\r\n5. Our Obligations to You and Limitations on Liability\r\n5.1\r\nWe cannot guarantee that the platform will always be fully operational or error free and so We do not accept responsibility for any defects that may exist or for any costs, loss of profits, loss of data or consequential losses arising from Your use of or inability to access the Web site.\r\n\r\n5.2\r\nWe make no warranty that the use of the platform will meet Your requirements or that use of the platform will be uninterrupted, timely, secure or error-free, that defects will be corrected, or that the platform or the server that makes it available are free of viruses or bugs or represents the full functionality, accuracy, reliability of the materials or as to results or the accuracy of any information obtained by You through the platform. \r\n\r\n5.3\r\nWe do not assess or endorse any of the material submitted to Us and/or posted on the platform including the accuracy or reliability of any text, information, data, representations, statements or other material whatsoever.\r\n\r\n5.5\r\nWe may provide links to other Web sites or resources and may post, accept the posting of or make available content provided by third parties ("Third Party Content"). We do not accept responsibility for the Third Party Content and do not and cannot be deemed to have endorsed any Third Party Content. In particular, You acknowledge that We will not be party to any transaction or contract with a third party that You may enter into and that We shall have no liability to You in respect of any such transaction, whether arising in contract, tort, under statute or otherwise. You undertake that You will not involve Us in any dispute between You and the third party.\r\n\r\n5.6\r\nWe will at all times comply with Our privacy policy (see below).\r\n\r\n6. Our Rights\r\nWe reserve the right to:\r\n\r\n6.1\r\ndeny or suspend Your registration  in the and/or access to the platform or any part thereof if Your participation in the platform and/or use of the platform is deemed by Us against the interests of other users or in breach of these Terms;\r\n\r\n6.2\r\nmodify or withdraw, temporarily or permanently, the platform (or any part thereof) with or without notice to You and You confirm that We shall not be liable to You or any third party for any modification to or withdrawal of the platform;\r\n\r\n6.3\r\nchange these terms and conditions at any point in time without giving reasons, save for the case that this is unreasonable for You. We will inform You about changes of the terms and conditions in time. If You do not object to the new terms and conditions within two (2) weeks’ time after having been informed, the new terms and conditions will be regarded as having been confirmed by You. When informing You of a change in the terms and conditions, we will also inform You of your right of objection and the meaning of the objection period.\r\n\r\n6.4\r\nrefuse to place any content or material provided by You onto the platform in Our sole discretion and to remove any content or material from the platform once uploaded in Our sole discretion.\r\n\r\n7. General\r\n7.1\r\nIf any part of the Terms shall be deemed unlawful, void or for any reason unenforceable, then that provision shall be deemed to be severable from the Terms and shall not affect the validity and enforceability of any of the remaining provisions of the Terms.\r\n\r\n7.2\r\nNo waiver by Us shall be construed as a waiver of any proceeding or succeeding breach of any provision.\r\n\r\n7.3\r\nEach provision of the Terms shall be construed as separately applying and surviving even if for any reason one or other of those provisions is held to be inapplicable or unenforceable in any circumstances.\r\n\r\n8. Contact Information\r\ninfo@central-community.eu\r\n \r\n', 'Terms of use', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'terms-of-use', '', '', '2014-04-04 16:45:55', '2014-04-04 16:45:55', '', 0, 'http://gaia.cybion.eu/cecommunity/?page_id=71', 0, 'page', '', 0),
